.TH "mem_cgroup_scan_tasks" 9 "mem_cgroup_scan_tasks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mem_cgroup_scan_tasks \- iterate over tasks of a memory cgroup hierarchy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mem_cgroup_scan_tasks
.BI "(struct mem_cgroup *memcg "  ","
.BI "int (*fn)(struct task_struct *, void *) "  ","
.BI "void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "memcg" 12
hierarchy root
.IP "fn" 12
function to call for each task
.IP "arg" 12
argument passed to \fIfn\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function iterates over tasks attached to \fImemcg\fP or to any of its
descendants and calls \fIfn\fP for each task. If \fIfn\fP returns a non-zero
value, the function breaks the iteration loop and returns the value.
Otherwise, it will iterate over all tasks and return 0.

This function must not be called for the root memory cgroup.
